13 (3) “Program” means the Therapeutic Child Care Grant Program.
14 (b) There is a Therapeutic Child Care Grant Program in the State.
15 (c) (1) The purpose of the Program is to provide grants to providers that
16 specialize in providing child care and early childhood education to children under the age
17 of 6 years who have developmental delays, physical disabilities, or delays in social,
18 emotional, or behavioral functioning.
19 (2) The Department shall administer the Program.
20 (3) On or before August 15 each year, the Department shall award grants
21 under this section.
22 (d) (1) For each of fiscal years 2023 through 2025, AND FOR FISCAL YEAR
23 2027 AND EACH FISCAL YEAR THEREAFTER, the Governor shall include in the annual
24 budget bill an appropriation of $3,700,000 to the Program.
25 (2) In awarding grants under the Program, the Department shall
26 distribute:
27 (i) $1,283,000 to existing providers in the same amount as was
28 provided in fiscal year 2022;
29 (ii) $1,917,000 to existing providers in the same proportion as was
30 provided in fiscal year 2022 to provide additional services; and

